10.1 Composition of common stock

Following the cancellation of 50 million registered shares of no par value of the Company (Siemens shares) in February 2023, the Company’s capital stock amounts to €2.400 billion (as of September 30, 2023), divided into 800 million Siemens shares. The shares are fully paid in. All shares confer the same rights and obligations. The shareholders’ rights and obligations are governed in detail by the provisions of the German Stock Corporation Act, in particular by Sections 12, 53a et seq., 118 et seq. and 186 of the German Stock Corporation Act.